column1: A change log showing journals withdrawn from DOAJ from 1st February 2024
A journal may be withdrawn from DOAJ for the following reasons:

Journal is no longer Open Access; Inactive (has not published in the last calendar year); Has not published enough articles this calendar year; Ceased publishing; Website URL no longer works; Journal not adhering to Best practice; Changed publisher but hasn't supplied new URLs/site
This document is a change log. It records an event in time and may not reflect the current status of a journal. A journal title may appear on both sheets and more than once.
